<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-07-18T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-07-18T02:00:00-05:00" n="221" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d221">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 P. W./264: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-18T16:00:00+09:00">July 18,
                                    1941—4 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received July 18—6:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1026. For the Acting Secretary. Department’s 404, July 16, 6 p.m.<note n="30" xml:id="d221fn30">Not printed, but see memorandum dated July
                                15, <ref target="frus1931-41v02#pg_506">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol.
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, pp. 506</ref>, <ref target="frus1931-41v02#pg_508">508</ref>–<ref target="frus1931-41v02#pg_509">509</ref>.</note> It would seem
                            that the Japanese Ambassador’s interpretation of article 3 of the
                            Tripartite Treaty is substantially that of the Prime Minister (please
                            see Embassy’s 924, July 2nd, 7 p.m.<note n="31" xml:id="d221fn31">
                                <hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_991">p.
                                991</ref>.</note>) and not that of Mr. Matsuoka. (Please see
                            Embassy’s 673, May 14, 5 p.m.<note n="32" xml:id="d221fn32">
                                <ref target="frus1931-41v02#pg_145">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol.
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 145</ref>.</note> and 707,
                            May 19, 10 p.m.<note n="32a" xml:id="d221fn32a">
                                <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_204">p.
                                204</ref>.</note>)</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>